---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Terms of Service"
  description="Terms of Service of Perceptum B.V. — duration, termination, pricing, ownership, and liability."
>
  <section class="gradient-navy relative overflow-hidden -mt-20 pt-20">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 opacity-[0.03]" style="background-image: radial-gradient(circle, white 1px, transparent 1px); background-size: 40px 40px;"></div>
    <div class="container-narrow mx-auto px-6 py-20 md:py-28 relative z-10">
      <h1 class="heading-xl text-white mb-6">Terms of Service</h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-slate-300 max-w-2xl">
        Clear, fair, customer-friendly.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-slate-400">
        <a href="/voorwaarden/" class="hover:text-white underline">Nederlandse versie</a>
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="relative h-12 md:h-20">
      <svg class="absolute bottom-0 w-full h-full" viewBox="0 0 1440 80" fill="none" preserveAspectRatio="none">
        <path d="M0 80L720 40L1440 80H0Z" fill="#f8fafc"/>
      </svg>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-padding">
    <div class="container-narrow mx-auto">
      <div class="max-w-3xl space-y-12">

        <div>
          <p class="text-lg text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
            These terms apply to all services Perceptum B.V. delivers: building your website, maintaining that website, and operating the Perceptum suite. We keep it short, clear, and honest.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-slate-500"><strong>Version 1.0 &middot; 30 April 2026</strong></p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="heading-md text-navy-900 mb-4">1. Who and what</h2>
          <div class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed space-y-3">
            <p>
              Perceptum B.V., Gooweg 14, 2203 AB Noordwijk, The Netherlands &mdash; Chamber of Commerce 76903885 &mdash; VAT NL860833306B01.
              Reachable through <a href="mailto:wijnand@perceptum.nl" class="text-accent hover:underline">wijnand@perceptum.nl</a>.
            </p>
            <p>
              "You" means the entrepreneur or organisation that hires us. "We" means Perceptum.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="heading-md text-navy-900 mb-4">2. What you get</h2>
          <div class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed space-y-3">
            <p>What exactly you get is documented in a quote or delivery document. By default our website service includes:</p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 pl-2">
              <li>A working website on your own domain</li>
              <li>Hosting and SSL</li>
              <li>Maintenance and security</li>
              <li>Access to the Perceptum suite (see §3)</li>
              <li>Response to questions within one business day</li>
            </ul>
            <p>In case of conflict between these terms and your quote, the quote prevails.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="heading-md text-navy-900 mb-4">3. The Perceptum suite</h2>
          <div class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed space-y-3">
            <p>
              The Perceptum suite is a continuously developed package of tools: Analytics, Formbridge (form backend), Chatbot, ConsentBridge (cookie consent), WebScan (technical audit), SpeedGuard (performance), UptimeGuard (availability), SocialProof, ReviewBridge (review management), Pinpoint (visual feedback), Content Machine, and Dashboard.
            </p>
            <p>
              Not every tool is always in every bundle. We add tools as they become production-ready and fit your situation. We do not remove active functionality without at least 30 days' notice.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="heading-md text-navy-900 mb-4">4. Duration and termination</h2>
          <div class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed space-y-3">
            <p>
              Our service continues until you terminate. No automatic multi-year renewals, no lock-in clauses.
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 pl-2">
              <li>Notice period: one month, by email to <a href="mailto:wijnand@perceptum.nl" class="text-accent hover:underline">wijnand@perceptum.nl</a>.</li>
              <li>Upon termination, your website remains live until the end of the current month.</li>
              <li>After termination we hand over your website source code, content, and all data you provided or generated within 30 days (right to data portability, GDPR art. 20).</li>
              <li>OAuth integrations (Google Business Profile, payment providers) we delete within 24 hours after termination.</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
              If we default or commit a material security failure, you may terminate immediately without notice.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="heading-md text-navy-900 mb-4">5. What you pay</h2>
          <div class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed space-y-3">
            <p>Prices are in your quote. By default:</p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 pl-2">
              <li>One-off setup fee for building your website</li>
              <li>Monthly amount for hosting, maintenance, and the Perceptum suite</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
              We invoice monthly in advance. Payment term: 14 days. Upon late payment, we first send a reminder, then a notice, and upon continued delay we suspend service (your website stays live, but new changes pause).
            </p>
            <p>
              We do not raise prices without reason. For a general price increase we inform you at least 60 days in advance and you may terminate within 30 days at the current rate.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="heading-md text-navy-900 mb-4">6. Ownership and usage rights</h2>
          <div class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed space-y-3">
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 pl-2">
              <li><strong>You own your own content</strong> — texts, photos, customer data, form submissions.</li>
              <li><strong>We retain ownership of the Perceptum suite</strong> as software. You have a right of use as long as our service runs.</li>
              <li><strong>The website source code</strong> we build for you, you may take with you upon termination. You have a perpetual right of use.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="heading-md text-navy-900 mb-4">7. What we promise (and don't)</h2>
          <div class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed space-y-4">
            <p><strong>We promise:</strong></p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 pl-2">
              <li>Working to current technical standards</li>
              <li>Responding to questions within one business day</li>
              <li>Security updates immediately after release</li>
              <li>Open communication and best-effort recovery during incidents</li>
            </ul>
            <p><strong>We do not promise:</strong></p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 pl-2">
              <li>100% uptime — we aim for 99.5% or better, but the internet and hosting providers experience occasional disruptions</li>
              <li>A specific position in search engines — we do what is technically and editorially possible, but Google determines ranking itself</li>
              <li>That external services (Google, Mollie, Resend) always work as they promise</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="heading-md text-navy-900 mb-4">8. Liability</h2>
          <div class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed space-y-3">
            <p>
              We do our work as carefully as possible, but mistakes can happen. Our liability is limited to the amount you have paid us in the past three months, with a maximum of € 5,000. We are not liable for lost revenue, lost customers, or indirect damage.
            </p>
            <p>
              This limitation does not apply in case of intent or gross negligence. For a demonstrable security failure that we should have prevented, we cover the costs of remediation and breach notification in full.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="heading-md text-navy-900 mb-4">9. Data processing</h2>
          <div class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed space-y-3">
            <p>
              When we process personal data of your customers on your behalf (for example through your forms or chatbot), we are processor and you are controller. Our data processing agreement is part of your quote.
            </p>
            <p>
              For data you provide to us yourself (your contact details, invoice details), we are controller. How we handle that is described in our <a href="/en/privacy/" class="text-accent hover:underline">Privacy Policy</a>.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="heading-md text-navy-900 mb-4">10. External services and integrations</h2>
          <div class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed space-y-3">
            <p>
              Our service integrates with external parties (Google, Mollie, Resend, Railway, Neon). For what you expose to these parties, their own terms also apply. We select parties that are GDPR-compliant and process EU data within the EU where possible.
            </p>
            <p>
              Specifically for Google Business Profile: you grant us access to your business profile through Google's own OAuth screen. What we do with it — and how to revoke it — is described in the <a href="/en/privacy/" class="text-accent hover:underline">Privacy Policy</a>.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="heading-md text-navy-900 mb-4">11. Changes</h2>
          <div class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
            <p>
              We change these terms only when necessary due to changes in our service or legislation. Substantive changes we announce at least 30 days in advance by email. For a change that is detrimental to you, you may terminate against that date at the current terms.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="heading-md text-navy-900 mb-4">12. Governing law</h2>
          <div class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
            <p>
              These terms are governed by Dutch law. Disputes we first present to each other in conversation; if we cannot resolve them together, the District Court of The Hague decides.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
